OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FIt will be largely cloudy as
OL,6,Fbands of rain push northeast in the
OL,7,Fmorning. The rain will turn showery
OL,8,Flater, these showers heavy and
OL,9,Fthundery at times. Windy around the
OL,10,Fcoast.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FShowery rain clearing east at
OL,13,Ffirst. Then clear spells and scattered
OL,14,Fshowers through the evening and
OL,15,Fovernight. Windy around the coast.
OL,16,
OL,17,CThursday:FBright or sunny spells and
OL,18,Fscattered showers, these most frequent
OL,19,Fin the west. Becoming mostly dry by
OL,20,Fthe evening as showers fade out.
OL,21,FBreezy around the coast.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
